1
00:00:33,660 --> 00:00:35,150
Stop!

2
00:00:35,230 --> 00:00:36,890
Get them!

3
00:00:59,320 --> 00:01:01,580
THANKS!

4
00:01:07,100 --> 00:01:09,530
Five billion with
nonsequential serial numbers.

5
00:01:09,600 --> 00:01:12,030
It's a shower of money!
Ya-hoo!

6
00:01:12,100 --> 00:01:15,230
Whoa! Yow, that's hot stuff.

7
00:01:15,300 --> 00:01:17,640
Come on. Bury me in it.

8
00:01:28,520 --> 00:01:29,880
What's wrong, Lupin?

9
00:01:29,950 --> 00:01:31,510
- Dump it.
- What?

10
00:01:31,590 --> 00:01:34,990
This is counterfeit.
Excellent quality too.

11
00:01:35,060 --> 00:01:37,150
All this?

12
00:01:37,230 --> 00:01:40,960
No way. We heisted this
from the vault of the national casino.

13
00:01:41,760 --> 00:01:44,100
- Goat bills.
- Goat bills?

14
00:01:44,170 --> 00:01:46,220
You mean
the legendary counterfeits?

15
00:01:46,300 --> 00:01:49,400
So they've made their way
into the national casinos now.

16
00:01:49,470 --> 00:01:52,270
Jigen! I've decided
what our next job will be.

17
00:01:52,340 --> 00:01:55,070
Why don't we have a little
pre-victory celebration?

18
00:01:59,610 --> 00:02:03,880
Darn it! Darn it! Darn it!

19
00:02:30,810 --> 00:02:35,750
I want to go with you

20
00:02:37,020 --> 00:02:41,980
<i>Searching for happiness</i>

21
00:02:42,790 --> 00:02:48,890
<i>No matter how hard the road
or how the night may grow cold</i>

22
00:02:48,960 --> 00:02:54,990
<i>I just want to wander on with you</i>

23
00:03:00,170 --> 00:03:06,270
<i>Who else is there to comfort and hold</i>

24
00:03:06,650 --> 00:03:12,420
<i>This lonely traveler
when their heart grows cold?</i>

25
00:03:12,790 --> 00:03:15,690
<i>Who else but you can make</i>

26
00:03:15,760 --> 00:03:20,160
<i>All my dreams come true?</i>

27
00:03:25,070 --> 00:03:29,830
<i>Like a raging fire</i>

28
00:03:31,210 --> 00:03:36,700
<i>My love for you burns</i>

29
00:03:37,080 --> 00:03:42,540
<i>All I want is for you
to know how I feel</i>

30
00:03:42,620 --> 00:03:48,780
<i>Make me your prisoner
and never let go</i>

31
00:04:38,170 --> 00:04:41,230
The Duchy of Cagliostro.
Never heard of it.

32
00:04:41,310 --> 00:04:43,400
Population: 3500.

33
00:04:43,480 --> 00:04:46,500
The world's smallest member
state of the United Nations.

34
00:04:46,580 --> 00:04:49,140
And this is the source
of the Goat bills, huh?

35
00:04:49,220 --> 00:04:51,810
It's a famous legend
in the underworld.

36
00:04:51,890 --> 00:04:54,410
This is the black hole of
the counterfeiting world.

37
00:04:54,490 --> 00:04:56,150
Black hole?

38
00:04:56,220 --> 00:04:59,820
No one who's gone in looking
around here has ever come back.

39
00:04:59,890 --> 00:05:02,190
Oh, sounds scary.

40
00:05:03,500 --> 00:05:05,160
I'm so scared I need a nap.

41
00:05:16,380 --> 00:05:18,180
Hey!

42
00:05:32,760 --> 00:05:35,750
Jeez!
This spare's totally bald.

43
00:05:52,550 --> 00:05:54,540
Peaceful, isn't it?

44
00:06:07,860 --> 00:06:09,800
- What the—
- Get in!

45
00:06:30,890 --> 00:06:32,680
- Which are we helping?
-The girl!

46
00:06:32,750 --> 00:06:33,780
Typical.

47
00:06:41,930 --> 00:06:43,920
- Get the tires.
- Gotcha.

48
00:07:06,120 --> 00:07:08,020
Damn!
That's no ordinary car.

49
00:07:17,060 --> 00:07:20,090
Yow! Well, this is
sure getting exciting.

50
00:07:20,170 --> 00:07:21,930
Going up!

51
00:07:38,790 --> 00:07:40,450
Got 'em!

52
00:07:42,990 --> 00:07:44,980
This time I won't use
an ordinary bullet.

53
00:07:54,670 --> 00:07:56,600
All right!

54
00:08:10,280 --> 00:08:12,180
She's fainted.

55
00:08:19,090 --> 00:08:21,760
- It's coming apart.
- Take the wheel.

56
00:09:32,800 --> 00:09:35,830
- No, let me go!
- Hey, don't. It's dangerous!

57
00:09:35,900 --> 00:09:37,960
Down! Look down!

58
00:09:42,940 --> 00:09:44,930
Yeah, that's better.
Just stay like that.

59
00:10:16,540 --> 00:10:18,910
Hello?

60
00:10:36,800 --> 00:10:38,990
Hello?

61
00:10:44,840 --> 00:10:46,600
Forgive me.

62
00:11:04,090 --> 00:11:06,890
Hey, Lupin.

63
00:11:07,800 --> 00:11:11,060
- Jeez, what happened to you?
- Where's my bride?

64
00:11:19,270 --> 00:11:21,610
Damn it!

65
00:11:21,680 --> 00:11:24,840
Who are those guys and
why are they after that girl?

66
00:11:31,650 --> 00:11:35,110
- It's a ring, isn't it?
- Funny, I could swear I've-

67
00:11:45,300 --> 00:11:46,360
What's wrong?

68
00:11:46,430 --> 00:11:50,170
When you saw that ring, you suddenly
got a weird look in your eyes.

69
00:12:19,070 --> 00:12:22,530
Hey, Lupin.
What do we want at this old castle?

70
00:12:28,440 --> 00:12:32,350
The same crest
that was on the ring. Lupin?

71
00:12:43,960 --> 00:12:46,890
Abandoned,
but not that long ago, either.

72
00:12:49,700 --> 00:12:50,860
Fire, huh?

73
00:12:50,930 --> 00:12:53,420
- Who's there?
- Just some passers-by.

74
00:12:53,500 --> 00:12:55,730
- Tourists?
- You could say that.

75
00:12:55,800 --> 00:13:00,140
I was under the impression that
this was the grand duke's palace, but—

76
00:13:00,210 --> 00:13:04,140
It still is, and it's no place for
strangers to be wandering around in.

77
00:13:04,210 --> 00:13:07,840
This is the grand duke's palace?
It's just a burnt-out shell.

78
00:13:09,880 --> 00:13:11,820
There was a fire seven years ago.

79
00:13:11,890 --> 00:13:14,120
The duke and his wife
were lost in it.

80
00:13:14,190 --> 00:13:17,390
Since then, the palace
has been left to go to ruin.

81
00:13:17,460 --> 00:13:20,550
That's strange. The grand duke
was like your king, right?

82
00:13:20,630 --> 00:13:22,360
Does that mean
you don't have a king now?

83
00:13:22,430 --> 00:13:26,330
There's a regent. They say
there's nothing to be concerned about.

84
00:13:26,400 --> 00:13:29,340
- Now hurry up and leave.
- Right.

85
00:13:31,170 --> 00:13:32,830
Hey, Lupin!

86
00:14:54,350 --> 00:14:56,290
She's grown.

87
00:15:24,890 --> 00:15:28,120
- Something wrong?
- Quit playing dumb.

88
00:15:29,460 --> 00:15:32,320
Pulling that "I'm a cool,
suffering loner" act, right?

89
00:15:32,390 --> 00:15:34,690
- Now talk!
- No. No!

90
00:15:37,800 --> 00:15:40,130
- Gonna talk?
-I talk!

91
00:16:04,790 --> 00:16:08,060
The castle of
Count Cagliostro, the regent.

92
00:16:08,130 --> 00:16:09,790
Look over there.

93
00:16:09,860 --> 00:16:11,850
No, down a little more.

94
00:16:13,000 --> 00:16:15,260
Past the aqueduct.

95
00:16:17,200 --> 00:16:18,870
That boat from before!

96
00:16:19,570 --> 00:16:21,510
The bride's in that castle.

97
00:16:21,580 --> 00:16:24,840
There's the floodgate over there.
It hasn't changed at all.

98
00:16:24,910 --> 00:16:28,110
You've broken
into that castle before?

99
00:16:29,420 --> 00:16:31,320
That was more than 10 years ago.

100
00:16:31,390 --> 00:16:34,180
I was looking for the secret
of the Goat bills.

101
00:16:34,250 --> 00:16:36,250
I was still a young punk,
just starting out.

102
00:16:36,320 --> 00:16:37,760
And? What happened?

103
00:16:37,820 --> 00:16:39,990
I got my butt royally kicked!

104
00:16:40,060 --> 00:16:43,120
Had to run away with
my tail between my legs.

105
00:16:56,280 --> 00:16:58,270
I didn't think
they used autogyros anymore.

106
00:16:58,350 --> 00:16:59,840
It's the count.

107
00:16:59,910 --> 00:17:01,940
C'mon. Let's find a room
for the night.

108
00:17:02,020 --> 00:17:03,680
Hey!

109
00:17:30,040 --> 00:17:33,410
- You were careless, Jodo.
- I beg your pardon, My Lord.

110
00:17:33,480 --> 00:17:36,070
It happened while they were
fitting the bridal gown.

111
00:17:36,150 --> 00:17:39,050
She escaped when the men
left her alone in the room.

112
00:17:40,190 --> 00:17:41,920
She's in the north tower now?

113
00:17:41,990 --> 00:17:45,930
Yes, My Lord.
She's been heavily sedated.

114
00:17:50,660 --> 00:17:53,260
- Foreigners?
- Yes, Lord.

115
00:17:53,330 --> 00:17:57,740
Two men.
They helped her to escape.

116
00:17:58,640 --> 00:18:02,100
Find them
and take care of them.

117
00:19:10,910 --> 00:19:12,900
The ring's gone.

118
00:19:29,830 --> 00:19:31,730
Summon Jodo!

119
00:19:52,920 --> 00:19:55,720
This inscription's in Capran,
a dead language.

120
00:19:55,790 --> 00:19:56,780
Capran?

121
00:19:56,860 --> 00:20:01,060
"When light and shadow are joined
once more, it shall be restored."

122
00:20:01,130 --> 00:20:02,790
AD 1517.

123
00:20:02,860 --> 00:20:04,920
The date's in Roman numerals.

124
00:20:05,000 --> 00:20:07,060
So that ring's 400 years old.

125
00:20:07,130 --> 00:20:09,630
- Sorry for the wait.
- Looks great!

126
00:20:09,700 --> 00:20:11,760
What is it
that you are looking at?

127
00:20:11,840 --> 00:20:14,030
Oh, nothing.
Just this old ring I found.

128
00:20:14,110 --> 00:20:15,910
I was wondering
if it was worth anything.

129
00:20:15,980 --> 00:20:19,440
Oh, it's pretty!
That's Lady Clarisse's crest.

130
00:20:19,510 --> 00:20:20,740
Clarisse?

131
00:20:20,810 --> 00:20:22,650
Look, that girl.

132
00:20:22,720 --> 00:20:26,580
See that photo?
It was taken when she was a child.

133
00:20:26,650 --> 00:20:29,490
She just came back
from the convent yesterday.

134
00:20:29,560 --> 00:20:32,550
- I'll bet she's really beautiful now.
- Convent?

135
00:20:32,630 --> 00:20:34,120
Don't you know about it?

136
00:20:34,190 --> 00:20:38,560
I thought you both were here to see
Lady Clarisse marry the count.

137
00:20:38,630 --> 00:20:42,500
Oh, I see. No wonder why
there are so many tourists here.

138
00:20:42,570 --> 00:20:44,730
Still, I feel sorry for Lady Clarisse.

139
00:20:44,800 --> 00:20:47,470
The count's known for
being a real playboy.

140
00:20:47,540 --> 00:20:51,440
Oh, really? Just like me.
Say, are you busy tonight?

141
00:20:58,490 --> 00:21:00,450
One of the count's men.

142
00:21:00,520 --> 00:21:03,080
His eyes lit up
when he saw that ring.

143
00:21:03,160 --> 00:21:06,420
Just having the bride isn't enough.
They want the ring too, right?

144
00:21:06,490 --> 00:21:08,890
Oh, no, you don't!

145
00:21:09,730 --> 00:21:14,170
You knew that girl this afternoon was
the grand duke's daughter, didn't you?

146
00:21:14,230 --> 00:21:16,500
Oh, didn't I mention that?

147
00:21:30,180 --> 00:21:34,850
"When light and shadow are joined
once more, it shall be restored," huh?

148
00:21:37,060 --> 00:21:40,460
Do you think it's a treasure
that'll be restored?

149
00:22:19,800 --> 00:22:22,200
Oh-ho!
The gang's all here!

150
00:22:23,300 --> 00:22:25,500
Why, you—

151
00:22:36,420 --> 00:22:37,780
My Magnum has no effect!

152
00:22:37,850 --> 00:22:39,910
These guys are professional killers.

153
00:22:56,970 --> 00:22:57,960
Move it!

154
00:23:10,280 --> 00:23:11,980
They had me worried for a while.

155
00:23:12,050 --> 00:23:13,950
They actually launched
a full-scale attack on us.

156
00:23:14,020 --> 00:23:15,610
There's more to this case
than meets the eye.

157
00:23:15,690 --> 00:23:17,280
Things are really gettin'
interesting now.

158
00:23:52,760 --> 00:23:54,630
This batch isn't very well made.

159
00:23:54,690 --> 00:23:57,320
The quality's just
getting worse, isn't it?

160
00:23:57,400 --> 00:23:59,060
Forgive me, sir.

161
00:23:59,130 --> 00:24:02,530
But it's unavoidable if we continue
to mass-produce them like we are.

162
00:24:03,300 --> 00:24:06,500
Redo them. However,
we can't miss our delivery date.

163
00:24:06,570 --> 00:24:07,970
- Yes, sir.
- Who's there?

164
00:24:12,610 --> 00:24:13,980
Jodo, My Lord.

165
00:24:14,050 --> 00:24:17,450
For the first time ever, I've failed you.
The rats escaped the trap.

166
00:24:20,390 --> 00:24:22,880
Jodo, what's that paper
you have on your back?

167
00:24:25,360 --> 00:24:27,990
What the—
When did he—

168
00:24:28,060 --> 00:24:30,000
Lupin!

169
00:24:30,060 --> 00:24:31,960
It's Lupin's calling card.

170
00:24:32,030 --> 00:24:35,130
- Read it.
- Yes, My Lord, But—

171
00:24:35,200 --> 00:24:37,300
Just do it.

172
00:24:38,140 --> 00:24:41,340
Yes, Lord.
"To the lecherous and greedy count.

173
00:24:41,410 --> 00:24:44,100
I shall take your bride.
The day I will come is near."

174
00:24:44,180 --> 00:24:46,170
Signed, Lupin the Third.

175
00:24:47,710 --> 00:24:49,810
It's good news, Jodo.

176
00:24:51,620 --> 00:24:55,150
Why don't we wait for this man
Lupin to come to us?

177
00:25:38,770 --> 00:25:41,230
Hi, there.
You sure came quick.

178
00:25:42,640 --> 00:25:43,970
What's the job?

179
00:25:49,480 --> 00:25:51,000
Goemon's arrived.

180
00:25:51,080 --> 00:25:54,340
So has someone else.
Take a look.

181
00:25:58,850 --> 00:26:01,980
What?
That's a Japanese police car.

182
00:26:02,060 --> 00:26:03,820
- It's Zenigata.
- What?

183
00:26:06,130 --> 00:26:07,990
Everybody out!

184
00:26:08,800 --> 00:26:10,460
Form up!

185
00:26:13,730 --> 00:26:16,570
And now the players
are all in place.

186
00:26:16,640 --> 00:26:18,630
Ow, hot! Hot!

187
00:26:26,580 --> 00:26:28,810
Forgive me
for interrupting your meal.

188
00:26:34,290 --> 00:26:36,620
I am Zenigata of Interpol.

189
00:26:36,690 --> 00:26:40,520
We've received a report that you've
gotten one of Lupin's calling cards.

190
00:26:43,030 --> 00:26:46,760
You no doubt mean the grandson
of that common thief, Arsene Lupin.

191
00:26:46,830 --> 00:26:51,000
Is Interpol in the habit of interrupting
peoples' breakfasts for such matters?

192
00:26:51,070 --> 00:26:53,510
Your Excellency,
you shouldn't make light of Lupin.

193
00:26:53,570 --> 00:26:55,600
If he says he's coming,
then he's definitely coming.

194
00:26:55,680 --> 00:26:57,200
Your wedding is in five days.

195
00:26:57,280 --> 00:27:01,040
Until then, please allow
my men to guard this castle.

196
00:27:03,550 --> 00:27:05,750
We have police in this country too.

197
00:27:05,820 --> 00:27:09,760
Although we have the refinement
to refer to them as the "royal guard."

198
00:27:09,820 --> 00:27:11,150
You summoned me, My Lord?

199
00:27:11,220 --> 00:27:15,130
Gustav, cooperate
with our Japanese guest.

200
00:27:15,190 --> 00:27:17,060
- You may leave.
- Yes, sir!

201
00:27:17,130 --> 00:27:18,790
Your Excellency,
I have one more question.

202
00:27:18,870 --> 00:27:21,840
Will you please tell me why
Lupin would be after your bride?

203
00:27:21,900 --> 00:27:26,700
Who knows?
Isn't finding that out your job?

204
00:27:27,770 --> 00:27:29,670
If you'll excuse me.

205
00:27:32,480 --> 00:27:36,810
Is it wise to have that man
inside the castle, My Lord?

206
00:27:36,880 --> 00:27:40,250
It doesn't matter. I have many
friends in Interpol as well.

207
00:27:40,320 --> 00:27:42,350
They'll be leaving soon.

208
00:27:45,260 --> 00:27:48,130
Good ol' Zenigata.
The archetypical Japanese man.

209
00:27:48,190 --> 00:27:49,860
Totally devoted to his work.

210
00:28:00,340 --> 00:28:02,170
What's that over there?

211
00:28:02,240 --> 00:28:04,040
Don't go any further.

212
00:28:04,110 --> 00:28:07,100
- What?
- Observe.

213
00:28:11,020 --> 00:28:14,210
If you don't wish to die,
don't wander around.

214
00:28:14,290 --> 00:28:16,380
Tell your men that too.

215
00:28:21,230 --> 00:28:23,960
Inspector. I'm picking up
anti-personnel radar here too.

216
00:28:24,030 --> 00:28:26,000
I've got a bad feeling
about this castle.

217
00:28:26,070 --> 00:28:29,430
There are too many security systems
here for a normal man to have.

218
00:28:32,070 --> 00:28:33,060
A woman?

219
00:28:33,140 --> 00:28:35,440
Oh, no!
Don't say you're bailing on us.

220
00:28:35,510 --> 00:28:38,140
Yeah, a girl's involved,
but that's not the whole story.

221
00:28:38,210 --> 00:28:40,540
You're saying that ring has
something to do with it?

222
00:28:40,610 --> 00:28:44,740
We'll find that out when we grab the
girl from that dirty old man, the count.

223
00:28:45,650 --> 00:28:49,020
Anyway, my Magnum
may not have worked on them...

224
00:28:49,090 --> 00:28:52,650
but between your sword
and this anti-tank rifle—

225
00:28:52,730 --> 00:28:54,220
Hey, there, Lupin.

226
00:28:54,290 --> 00:28:56,130
- You figured out a way in yet?
- Nope.

227
00:28:56,200 --> 00:28:59,650
That place is incredible.
A nest of lasers and radar.

228
00:28:59,730 --> 00:29:02,670
I see.
We may even need a tank.

229
00:29:02,740 --> 00:29:04,500
That's why you called in
Zenigata, right?

230
00:29:04,570 --> 00:29:06,470
What? Is that true, Lupin?

231
00:29:07,210 --> 00:29:09,640
Exactly!
You've got good intuition.

232
00:29:10,410 --> 00:29:13,110
Use poison to fight poison, eh?

233
00:29:18,250 --> 00:29:21,450
This is Cagliostro Castle.
This is where we are.

234
00:29:21,520 --> 00:29:24,010
This Roman aqueduct here
is still in use.

235
00:29:24,090 --> 00:29:26,750
It's the only way in.

236
00:29:26,830 --> 00:29:30,990
The aqueduct brings water from
this lake into the castle.

237
00:29:31,060 --> 00:29:35,630
I get it. And there won't be
any lasers in the water, right?

238
00:29:36,670 --> 00:29:39,160
Goemon. Stay on watch here.

239
00:29:46,050 --> 00:29:47,810
Careful. There's a hole.

240
00:29:59,190 --> 00:30:00,990
The first obstacle, huh?

241
00:30:03,030 --> 00:30:04,690
Let's go.

242
00:31:05,160 --> 00:31:06,680
Lupin!

243
00:31:25,280 --> 00:31:28,870
Whew! This must be the
machinery room for the clock.

244
00:31:28,950 --> 00:31:30,710
I wonder if that SOB
actually made it.

245
00:31:58,480 --> 00:32:00,240
What's that windmill for?

246
00:32:00,310 --> 00:32:04,080
Gustav said they use it
to bring water up into the castle.

247
00:32:05,890 --> 00:32:08,790
- And where does the water come out?
- A fountain on the upper cannon deck.

248
00:32:08,850 --> 00:32:10,950
- Come on!
- Yes, sir!

249
00:32:36,180 --> 00:32:37,170
Inspector!

250
00:32:37,250 --> 00:32:40,620
We just received orders from
Paris HQ, "Pull out at once."

251
00:32:40,690 --> 00:32:43,780
What? That's ridiculous!
I'll see about that.

252
00:32:57,900 --> 00:33:01,310
What? But we got a warning
that Lupin was coming, so—

253
00:33:01,370 --> 00:33:03,540
The count?

254
00:33:04,410 --> 00:33:08,350
I'm a cop, not a court jester!
I don't care if he likes us here or not—

255
00:33:09,020 --> 00:33:13,010
Hello? Hello?
Oh, for the love of—

256
00:33:13,090 --> 00:33:15,550
I'll talk to the count about this.

257
00:33:19,030 --> 00:33:21,760
Show me to the count.

258
00:33:25,730 --> 00:33:28,060
I need to see the count at once.

259
00:33:28,130 --> 00:33:30,130
Didn't you hear me?
Let me through!

260
00:33:30,200 --> 00:33:32,230
Stop it.

261
00:33:32,300 --> 00:33:35,710
Only trusted people are
allowed past this point.

262
00:33:36,580 --> 00:33:39,200
What? Are you saying
Interpol officers can't be trusted?

263
00:33:39,280 --> 00:33:41,770
I believe you've received
orders to pull out.

264
00:33:41,850 --> 00:33:43,180
I must ask you to leave.

265
00:33:44,620 --> 00:33:46,610
How did you know about that?

266
00:33:46,690 --> 00:33:50,590
We won't need any of you Orientals
to help us with Lupin. Now go.

267
00:33:53,690 --> 00:33:56,750
Oh, really? I see.
We're pulling out for now.

268
00:34:09,010 --> 00:34:11,070
Was I just here?

269
00:34:11,140 --> 00:34:12,980
- What?
- You idiot! That was Lupin!

270
00:34:13,050 --> 00:34:15,210
He disguised himself as me
so he could sneak in here!

271
00:34:15,280 --> 00:34:18,150
Couldn't a muscle-bound idiot
like you see through that getup?

272
00:34:18,220 --> 00:34:21,150
Why, that— Follow me!

273
00:34:22,090 --> 00:34:24,610
Don't let Lupin get away!

274
00:34:30,560 --> 00:34:31,830
Hold it!

275
00:34:34,630 --> 00:34:35,760
Lupin?

276
00:34:37,340 --> 00:34:40,240
Cut it out! It's Lupin!

277
00:34:40,310 --> 00:34:43,770
Save the Inspector!
Charge!

278
00:34:50,050 --> 00:34:52,250
Wow, that's wild.

279
00:34:53,220 --> 00:34:55,850
Cut it out! He's Lupin!

280
00:34:57,890 --> 00:34:59,480
Darn it!

281
00:35:15,270 --> 00:35:16,760
Lupin!

282
00:35:32,790 --> 00:35:34,450
Looks like we caught someone.

283
00:35:39,800 --> 00:35:42,790
That fool. He should have left
as soon as he could.

284
00:35:42,870 --> 00:35:45,060
- The guards are gone.
- Gustav!

285
00:35:45,140 --> 00:35:47,940
What's he doing,
leaving his post?

286
00:35:49,070 --> 00:35:51,170
- You stay here.
- Yes, sir!

287
00:35:52,980 --> 00:35:55,000
Sorry, Old Man.

288
00:35:56,650 --> 00:35:59,580
<i>You fool!</i>
Stop this uproar at once!

289
00:35:59,650 --> 00:36:03,180
Don't you understand?
Lupin did this to sneak in.

290
00:36:03,260 --> 00:36:04,750
Why, that—

291
00:36:09,230 --> 00:36:12,200
Let go. Let go of me!

292
00:36:19,100 --> 00:36:21,370
So that devil Lupin
made it in after all.

293
00:36:21,440 --> 00:36:23,270
I have no excuse, My Lord.

294
00:36:23,340 --> 00:36:27,250
Tell the inspector's men that
he went home ahead of them.

295
00:36:27,310 --> 00:36:31,220
It's not unheard of for people
to vanish while traveling, is it?

296
00:36:55,040 --> 00:36:56,530
Don't move.

297
00:36:58,480 --> 00:37:01,110
- Good evening, Fujiko.
- Lupin!

298
00:37:01,180 --> 00:37:04,510
There's nothing lovelier than a woman
who's absorbed in her work.

299
00:37:04,580 --> 00:37:06,480
So you made it in this far.

300
00:37:06,550 --> 00:37:09,350
That's all you say after a year apart?
You wound me, my dear.

301
00:37:09,420 --> 00:37:10,910
And after I looked all over for you.

302
00:37:10,990 --> 00:37:15,390
Lupin, you're looking
for the bride, aren't you?

303
00:37:15,460 --> 00:37:17,330
Oh, you know about that?

304
00:37:17,400 --> 00:37:21,060
I'll tell you where she is, but do you
promise to not interfere with my job?

305
00:37:21,130 --> 00:37:23,500
I won't!
I'd never dream of it.

306
00:37:23,570 --> 00:37:25,230
I wonder about that.

307
00:37:25,300 --> 00:37:27,500
She's being held
at the top of the north tower.

308
00:37:27,570 --> 00:37:30,270
Although it's impossible to get into.

309
00:37:34,050 --> 00:37:35,710
Lupin?

310
00:38:00,540 --> 00:38:03,770
Damn, they've really got her
locked up in a hell of a place.

311
00:41:02,320 --> 00:41:05,190
- Who's there?
- A thief.

312
00:41:05,960 --> 00:41:08,020
A thief?

313
00:41:12,000 --> 00:41:14,060
Good evening, Miss Bride.

314
00:41:15,370 --> 00:41:17,460
You! You're the man who—

315
00:41:17,540 --> 00:41:19,030
You forgot something.

316
00:41:23,180 --> 00:41:24,840
You came here just for this?

317
00:41:24,910 --> 00:41:27,070
But if the count finds you,
you'll be killed.

318
00:41:27,150 --> 00:41:31,410
No matter. To hunt and be hunted
is the nature of being a thief.

319
00:41:31,480 --> 00:41:33,540
I will leave once
I've finished my job.

320
00:41:33,620 --> 00:41:35,520
Your job?

321
00:41:36,560 --> 00:41:41,890
I wish I had something to give you,
but I'm a prisoner.

322
00:41:44,160 --> 00:41:45,890
Here. Take this.

323
00:41:49,130 --> 00:41:51,600
What I seek is a treasure...

324
00:41:51,670 --> 00:41:54,870
which an evil sorcerer
has locked inside a high tower.

325
00:41:58,440 --> 00:42:02,110
Will you allow this humble thief
to please steal it away?

326
00:42:02,180 --> 00:42:03,620
You mean me?

327
00:42:06,820 --> 00:42:10,720
Like I save precious gems which
have been locked away in a vault...

328
00:42:10,790 --> 00:42:14,120
I have come to take a girl
forced to be a bride against her will...

329
00:42:14,190 --> 00:42:16,920
and set her free
in the green fields outside.

330
00:42:17,930 --> 00:42:20,870
This all goes with being a thief.

331
00:42:21,830 --> 00:42:24,030
You've come to set me free?

332
00:42:38,620 --> 00:42:42,420
Thank you.
I appreciate what you're doing.

333
00:42:42,490 --> 00:42:46,690
But you don't know the terrible
secrets of the Cagliostro family.

334
00:42:49,230 --> 00:42:51,560
Please just leave me and go.

335
00:42:57,840 --> 00:43:00,810
Oh, how can this be?

336
00:43:00,870 --> 00:43:04,370
The girl believes in the
power of the evil sorcerer...

337
00:43:04,440 --> 00:43:07,240
yet she doesn't believe
in the power of the thief.

338
00:43:07,310 --> 00:43:09,300
Oh, if only she'd believe in him...

339
00:43:09,380 --> 00:43:12,610
the thief would be able
to fly through the air!

340
00:43:12,680 --> 00:43:16,120
He would be able drink
all the water in the lake!

341
00:43:41,050 --> 00:43:44,040
For now,
this is the best I can do.

342
00:44:18,480 --> 00:44:20,540
Mr. Thief!

343
00:44:20,620 --> 00:44:24,060
Hey!
Treat the lady gently, okay?

344
00:44:34,270 --> 00:44:37,930
Thank you so much for
returning the ring, my dear Lupin.

345
00:44:38,000 --> 00:44:41,200
Well, I appreciate
this warm welcome, Count.

346
00:44:41,270 --> 00:44:44,170
I'm afraid
you're going to disappear now.

347
00:44:44,240 --> 00:44:47,110
But can you really
make me vanish so easily?

348
00:44:48,050 --> 00:44:50,010
Stop it!
Don't hurt that man!

349
00:44:50,080 --> 00:44:54,210
I'll be fine, Miss. Remember,
believe in the power of the thief.

350
00:44:55,920 --> 00:44:57,290
Mr. Thief!

351
00:44:57,360 --> 00:45:02,090
Yup, I'm right here.
I'll be back soon.

352
00:45:03,900 --> 00:45:05,800
Well, now,
what game shall we play?

353
00:45:05,860 --> 00:45:07,860
It would be simple
to just rip you apart.

354
00:45:07,930 --> 00:45:10,430
However, I don't want
my bride's room to be stained...

355
00:45:10,500 --> 00:45:12,560
by the blood of a common thief.

356
00:45:12,640 --> 00:45:16,040
I'll make you regret
that you ever said that.

357
00:45:16,110 --> 00:45:18,980
Enough of your insolence.

358
00:45:26,280 --> 00:45:30,880
That hole leads to a hell
not one person has ever escaped from.

359
00:46:00,650 --> 00:46:04,280
That pretty face has already
lured a man to his doom.

360
00:46:04,360 --> 00:46:06,690
You can't deny the
Cagliostro blood inside of you.

361
00:46:08,590 --> 00:46:10,430
You'll make
a most fitting wife for me.

362
00:46:10,500 --> 00:46:13,160
Murderer!
You aren't human.

363
00:46:13,230 --> 00:46:15,030
You're right.

364
00:46:15,100 --> 00:46:19,090
My hands have blood on them
as do your own.

365
00:46:19,170 --> 00:46:23,300
The family of the count has always served
in the shadow of the grand duke's.

366
00:46:23,380 --> 00:46:27,010
Performing its plots and assassinations.
Supporting this country.

367
00:46:27,080 --> 00:46:29,050
Let me go!
You're disgusting.

368
00:46:31,680 --> 00:46:34,120
Don't pretend you don't know.

369
00:46:35,190 --> 00:46:37,920
You, too, are a Cagliostro.

370
00:46:37,990 --> 00:46:42,690
Within your body, like mine,
flows the ancient blood of the Goat.

371
00:46:44,860 --> 00:46:50,320
Clarisse, for 400 years,
light has been separated from shadow...

372
00:46:50,400 --> 00:46:55,000
but now the two houses of
Cagliostro will be reunited.

373
00:46:55,070 --> 00:46:57,010
Look.

374
00:46:57,080 --> 00:47:00,910
When the gold goat that
marks my house is joined...

375
00:47:01,680 --> 00:47:04,080
with the silver goat
of your house...

376
00:47:04,150 --> 00:47:07,680
the treasure hidden by our ancestors
will be restored.

377
00:47:07,750 --> 00:47:09,880
I heard him!

378
00:47:09,960 --> 00:47:12,720
<i>- He's marrying her to get the treasure.</i>
- It's him!

379
00:47:12,790 --> 00:47:16,730
<i>The counterfeiting count.
Everything he says or does is fake!</i>

380
00:47:17,360 --> 00:47:20,330
<i>That girl happens to be
a sweet, wonderful person.</i>

381
00:47:22,700 --> 00:47:25,690
- Mr. Thief?
<i>- Yup! I'm just fine.</i>

382
00:47:25,770 --> 00:47:29,170
Since the girl believed in me,
I was able to fly through the air.

383
00:47:29,240 --> 00:47:31,900
Mr. Thief is coming
to steal you away.

384
00:47:31,980 --> 00:47:33,910
<i>- Wait for me, okay?</i>
- Yes.

385
00:47:33,980 --> 00:47:36,380
<i>Damn it, it's the ring!</i>

386
00:47:36,450 --> 00:47:38,350
Give me that.

387
00:47:39,920 --> 00:47:42,350
Okay, Count, listen up!

388
00:47:43,120 --> 00:47:44,780
<i>I've got the real ring.</i>

389
00:47:44,860 --> 00:47:49,020
<i>If you lay one finger on that girl,
your precious ring will end up like this!</i>

390
00:47:51,160 --> 00:47:53,390
It's a fake!

391
00:48:03,680 --> 00:48:05,540
Why, you—

392
00:48:05,610 --> 00:48:08,550
You really do
treat people like crap!

393
00:48:08,610 --> 00:48:10,310
- Did he fall?
- Probably.

394
00:48:10,380 --> 00:48:11,370
Make sure.

395
00:48:11,450 --> 00:48:14,250
Down there
isn't a place for the living.

396
00:48:14,320 --> 00:48:16,520
If we leave him alone,
he'll surely die.

397
00:48:16,590 --> 00:48:20,490
- He still has the ring.
- As you wish, My Lord.

398
00:48:20,560 --> 00:48:22,050
Just wait.

399
00:48:22,130 --> 00:48:25,760
I'll bring your dear thief
back to you in pieces!

400
00:49:41,340 --> 00:49:46,000
Killing and killing for 400 years.
Rest in peace, all of you.

401
00:49:50,750 --> 00:49:53,310
MARCH 14, 1904.
HERE GENNOSUKE KAWAKAMI.

402
00:49:53,390 --> 00:49:56,720
SPY FOR THE JAPANESE ARMY,
MET HIS END. AVENGE ME.

403
00:50:11,170 --> 00:50:13,040
Lupin!

404
00:50:13,100 --> 00:50:15,840
Why, you—
Come along quietly!

405
00:50:15,910 --> 00:50:17,710
Old Man, you're still alive.

406
00:50:17,780 --> 00:50:20,470
Tell me. Where's the exit?
How did you get in here?

407
00:50:20,550 --> 00:50:22,780
I fell in, same as you.

408
00:50:25,750 --> 00:50:28,520
You look like you've been
walking around for a long time.

409
00:50:28,590 --> 00:50:31,450
Shut up!
I won't take pity from a thief.

410
00:50:31,520 --> 00:50:35,430
Well, we may as well relax.
There's no way out of here.

411
00:50:36,260 --> 00:50:38,420
'Scuse me, pal.

412
00:50:39,630 --> 00:50:42,070
Hey, Old Man, you got a light?

413
00:50:42,130 --> 00:50:46,370
Lupin, what's with all these bodies?
I doubt this is a graveyard.

414
00:50:46,440 --> 00:50:48,810
Take a look at that wall.

415
00:50:55,810 --> 00:50:57,910
Th-This is—

416
00:51:00,190 --> 00:51:02,310
Rest in peace.

417
00:51:04,020 --> 00:51:06,510
I thought there was something
suspicious about this castle...

418
00:51:06,590 --> 00:51:09,530
but what sort of secret is worth
this much trouble to hide?

419
00:51:09,590 --> 00:51:11,930
Hey, Lupin.
Is that what you're after here?

420
00:51:12,000 --> 00:51:13,730
That's what Fujiko's after.

421
00:51:13,800 --> 00:51:16,930
I hope she doesn't end up
like these bodies in here.

422
00:51:17,000 --> 00:51:19,330
Anyway, running around
in a panic won't help us.

423
00:51:19,400 --> 00:51:22,000
Good night, Old Man.

424
00:51:36,120 --> 00:51:37,780
It's cold!

425
00:51:37,860 --> 00:51:40,480
Man, look how long it's been.
How do things look?

426
00:51:40,560 --> 00:51:42,460
Still no movement.

427
00:51:44,500 --> 00:51:46,660
Then I guess we just wait.

428
00:53:23,930 --> 00:53:25,920
They're taking too long.

429
00:53:27,070 --> 00:53:29,060
Mr. Jodo!

430
00:53:31,140 --> 00:53:33,040
They've found it!

431
00:53:37,180 --> 00:53:38,640
Heave-ho!

432
00:53:42,110 --> 00:53:43,980
Curse you, Lupin!

433
00:53:51,420 --> 00:53:53,390
These are coffins.

434
00:54:02,630 --> 00:54:04,860
What is all this?

435
00:54:16,920 --> 00:54:20,910
These are Japanese 10,000 yen bills.
Looks like this all is.

436
00:54:22,950 --> 00:54:27,080
These are really well-made.
Hey, Old Man, look!

437
00:54:28,190 --> 00:54:29,850
West German 1,000 mark bills.

438
00:54:29,930 --> 00:54:31,830
Pounds. Dollars.

439
00:54:31,900 --> 00:54:35,460
Francs. Rubles. Rupees.
Pesos. Crowns. Lira.

440
00:54:36,700 --> 00:54:40,100
They've even got won!
It's the whole world in here.

441
00:54:41,240 --> 00:54:45,870
They're making counterfeits.
Lupin, is this the castle's secret?

442
00:54:45,940 --> 00:54:48,380
Exactly. This is the
source of the counterfeits...

443
00:54:48,450 --> 00:54:51,680
that were supposedly better
than the originals: the Goat bills.

444
00:54:52,450 --> 00:54:54,580
<i>The counterfeit money
which inevitably moved...</i>

445
00:54:54,650 --> 00:54:57,590
<i>in the shadow of the upheavals
of medieval Europe.</i>

446
00:54:57,660 --> 00:54:59,710
<i>It caused the collapse
of the Bourbon dynasty...</i>

447
00:54:59,790 --> 00:55:01,890
<i>became Napoleon's
source of funding...</i>

448
00:55:01,960 --> 00:55:06,860
<i>and eventually triggered
the world bank panic of 1927.</i>

449
00:55:06,930 --> 00:55:08,870
<i>Appearing
on the backstage of history...</i>

450
00:55:08,930 --> 00:55:11,060
<i>as the star of the black hole:
the Goat bills.</i>

451
00:55:11,140 --> 00:55:14,260
<i>Of all the people who came here
looking for their source...</i>

452
00:55:14,340 --> 00:55:17,040
<i>not a single one of them
ever returned.</i>

453
00:55:18,610 --> 00:55:20,440
I've heard rumors about this...

454
00:55:20,510 --> 00:55:23,500
but who'd ever believe an
independent nation was running it?

455
00:55:23,580 --> 00:55:25,380
What're you gonna do,
Old Man?

456
00:55:25,450 --> 00:55:27,980
After seeing this,
there's no going back.

457
00:55:28,050 --> 00:55:30,920
I know!
It makes my cop's blood burn.

458
00:55:32,060 --> 00:55:34,890
How about a truce
until we get out of here?

459
00:55:34,960 --> 00:55:38,290
Very well, but I won't
help you steal anything.

460
00:55:38,360 --> 00:55:41,330
And after we're out of here,
I swear I'll arrest you.

461
00:55:41,400 --> 00:55:45,460
It's settled, then.
Let's shake on it.

462
00:55:47,310 --> 00:55:49,930
- I won't be corrupted.
- Corrupted?

463
00:55:57,480 --> 00:56:01,180
- Miss Fujiko.
- The time's come to say good bye.

464
00:56:03,020 --> 00:56:04,350
Who are you?

465
00:56:04,420 --> 00:56:06,910
To all appearances,
I'm the one woman...

466
00:56:06,990 --> 00:56:09,890
who is employed here
in the castle as your servant.

467
00:56:09,960 --> 00:56:13,960
But in reality, I'm a lady spy who's
looking for this castle's secret.

468
00:56:14,030 --> 00:56:17,560
I was hoping to stay a little longer,
but now Lupin's come.

469
00:56:17,640 --> 00:56:19,930
Everything's fallen apart,
so I'm leaving.

470
00:56:20,000 --> 00:56:22,170
You know that man?

471
00:56:22,240 --> 00:56:23,900
Only too well.

472
00:56:23,980 --> 00:56:27,040
Sometimes we're allies,
at others we're enemies.

473
00:56:27,110 --> 00:56:29,580
Occasionally, we're even lovers.

474
00:56:29,650 --> 00:56:32,550
The guy's a natural born lady-killer.
Watch your step around him.

475
00:56:32,620 --> 00:56:34,240
He walked out on you?

476
00:56:34,320 --> 00:56:37,550
Oh, hardly.
I walked out on him.

477
00:56:41,130 --> 00:56:43,060
There's smoke coming
from the trapdoor.

478
00:56:43,130 --> 00:56:44,620
Afire?

479
00:56:47,330 --> 00:56:49,530
It's coming from underground.

480
00:56:51,640 --> 00:56:54,000
- Movement.
- He's started.

481
00:57:02,010 --> 00:57:03,910
Fire! Fire!

482
00:57:06,980 --> 00:57:09,480
Trouble! A fire's started in
the underground printing plant.

483
00:57:09,550 --> 00:57:11,990
- What? Put it out at once!
- Yes, My Lord.

484
00:57:12,060 --> 00:57:15,190
Close that blasted door!
The rest of you, go, too.

485
00:57:15,960 --> 00:57:18,160
Damn you, Jodo.
Have you failed me again?

486
00:57:23,940 --> 00:57:26,770
Hurry up, Old Man!
Our guests will be here soon.

487
00:57:26,840 --> 00:57:29,210
Evidence. I need evidence!

488
00:57:34,850 --> 00:57:37,320
Curse you, Lupin!

489
00:57:39,280 --> 00:57:42,280
Look for them!
They may still be in here.

490
00:57:45,760 --> 00:57:48,950
Have no fear! Forward!

491
00:57:53,460 --> 00:57:55,190
It's Lupin. After him!

492
00:57:55,270 --> 00:57:57,000
You put out the fire.

493
00:58:04,710 --> 00:58:06,840
The chapel!

494
00:58:12,580 --> 00:58:14,980
- Mr. Thief!
- Lupin. And Zenigata?

495
00:58:21,760 --> 00:58:24,560
They're trying to steal
the autogyro!

496
00:58:27,930 --> 00:58:29,960
- You fool!
-You can punish me later.

497
00:58:30,030 --> 00:58:32,830
They're trying to take
Lady Clarisse. Hurry!

498
00:58:40,680 --> 00:58:42,170
Hurry up!

499
00:58:48,990 --> 00:58:50,420
Halt!

500
00:58:50,490 --> 00:58:52,460
Why, you—
Never mess with Tokyo Metro!

501
00:58:52,520 --> 00:58:54,180
Old Man, get on!

502
00:59:03,470 --> 00:59:05,060
So long!

503
00:59:05,140 --> 00:59:07,330
Old Man, we have to
make a little detour.

504
00:59:07,410 --> 00:59:09,430
I will not cooperate
in a kidnapping for ransom.

505
00:59:09,510 --> 00:59:10,870
This isn't business.

506
00:59:16,880 --> 00:59:19,010
They're coming this way.

507
00:59:36,570 --> 00:59:39,000
Bulletproof glass!

508
00:59:41,040 --> 00:59:43,230
We can't open it.
Please just leave me!

509
00:59:53,420 --> 00:59:56,250
- Old Man, take over, would you?
- What? Lupin, wait!

510
00:59:56,320 --> 00:59:58,690
I can't fly this thing!

511
01:00:02,230 --> 01:00:04,720
- Clarisse?
- Mr. Thief!

512
01:00:04,800 --> 01:00:07,200
Your ride's here.
Fujiko, throw me a rope!

513
01:00:07,270 --> 01:00:09,360
Quit bossing me around!

514
01:00:16,670 --> 01:00:17,660
Miss Fujiko!

515
01:00:19,580 --> 01:00:21,070
Hurry!

516
01:00:33,960 --> 01:00:35,890
<i>- Mr. Thief!
- Okay, you're safe now.</i>

517
01:00:41,300 --> 01:00:43,200
Old Man! This way!

518
01:00:43,270 --> 01:00:46,640
What do you think
I'm trying to do, you idiot?

519
01:00:51,410 --> 01:00:52,900
Okay, that's it!

520
01:01:15,900 --> 01:01:17,390
Lupin!

521
01:01:18,900 --> 01:01:21,430
Don't move,
you meddling woman!

522
01:01:25,380 --> 01:01:29,370
Fujiko, I'll take my time
interrogating you later.

523
01:01:29,450 --> 01:01:32,280
-Jodo, finish Lupin off.
- Yes, sir.

524
01:01:32,350 --> 01:01:33,750
No! Don't shoot!

525
01:01:33,820 --> 01:01:36,250
If you kill him,
you'll kill me too.

526
01:01:36,320 --> 01:01:37,690
Fire.

527
01:01:57,480 --> 01:02:00,600
I admire your devotion, Clarisse.

528
01:02:04,780 --> 01:02:07,770
Get the ring back
and come here.

529
01:02:07,850 --> 01:02:10,690
Become my wife
and I will let Lupin live.

530
01:02:11,720 --> 01:02:16,390
Or you can both die here together.
The choice is yours.

531
01:02:26,400 --> 01:02:28,930
Mr. Thief, give me the ring.

532
01:02:29,010 --> 01:02:32,810
No, Clarisse. Don't do it.

533
01:02:32,880 --> 01:02:35,740
Under his collar.
Lupin always hides things there.

534
01:02:36,510 --> 01:02:39,070
Darn it, Fujiko!

535
01:02:51,660 --> 01:02:53,150
I have the ring.

536
01:02:53,230 --> 01:02:56,760
Let this man and Fujiko go,
or I'll throw it into the lake.

537
01:02:56,830 --> 01:03:00,600
You have my word.
Now put the ring on and come here.

538
01:03:00,670 --> 01:03:03,500
- Shall I shoot?
- Wait until we have the ring.

539
01:03:13,620 --> 01:03:15,550
Lupin!

540
01:03:18,920 --> 01:03:20,550
Shoot!
Don't let them escape!

541
01:03:25,460 --> 01:03:28,230
Liar!
You said you'd let them go.

542
01:03:28,300 --> 01:03:32,260
Let them go after they've seen
the underground plant?

543
01:03:38,880 --> 01:03:41,740
At last, it's mine.

544
01:03:56,960 --> 01:04:00,760
Lupin, you owe me for today.
See you.

545
01:04:07,070 --> 01:04:10,740
We didn't even get to join in,
and we're already pulling out!

546
01:04:14,250 --> 01:04:17,510
Oh, it's no use.
Jump for it!

547
01:04:30,490 --> 01:04:32,960
Once again,
I cut a worthless object.

548
01:04:35,000 --> 01:04:38,330
Lupin! Don't you dare die
before I get to arrest you!

549
01:04:41,910 --> 01:04:45,310
Whatever we do,
it'll mean trouble.

550
01:04:45,380 --> 01:04:48,280
It's some sort of plot.

551
01:04:49,280 --> 01:04:51,440
Give the order for us to go in!

552
01:04:51,520 --> 01:04:54,950
Look how clear all this evidence is.
I saw it myself.

553
01:04:55,020 --> 01:04:57,220
The latest printing equipment,
all over the room like—

554
01:04:57,290 --> 01:04:59,450
We understand that!

555
01:05:00,960 --> 01:05:03,830
This is a high-level
political problem...

556
01:05:03,890 --> 01:05:07,630
and Interpol's jurisdiction is
limited to international crime.

557
01:05:07,700 --> 01:05:10,330
Chief, the crime is clear!

558
01:05:10,400 --> 01:05:12,060
You don't understand.

559
01:05:12,140 --> 01:05:14,760
The one committing it is an independent
member of the United Nations.

560
01:05:14,840 --> 01:05:17,640
Even Interpol can't conduct
a forcible criminal investigation.

561
01:05:17,710 --> 01:05:20,610
Besides that,
the situation isn't in our favor at all.

562
01:05:20,680 --> 01:05:24,810
Have you seen the pictures on the
front pages of the world's newspapers?

563
01:05:24,880 --> 01:05:27,870
"Count bravely defends his bride!

564
01:05:27,950 --> 01:05:30,350
Lupin's attempt to kidnap
Princess Clarisse fails!"

565
01:05:30,420 --> 01:05:33,390
Along with reports of a henchman
disguised as Zenigata.

566
01:05:33,460 --> 01:05:35,550
That was really me!

567
01:05:35,630 --> 01:05:39,030
Wasn't that a bit rash
for an officer in your position?

568
01:05:39,100 --> 01:05:42,000
The truth has to be told!

569
01:05:42,070 --> 01:05:45,530
The problem is whether
world opinion will believe you.

570
01:05:45,600 --> 01:05:46,930
There's no way we can win.

571
01:05:47,000 --> 01:05:50,800
The count has many friends among
the Western governments, does he not?

572
01:05:50,870 --> 01:05:53,900
The truth may cause trouble
for a lot of nations.

573
01:05:53,980 --> 01:05:56,450
Yes, considering the evidence
that these mass-produced...

574
01:05:56,510 --> 01:05:59,010
counterfeit dollars were
ordered by a certain country!

575
01:05:59,080 --> 01:06:01,880
And these counterfeit rubles
weren't ordered by the CIA?

576
01:06:01,950 --> 01:06:03,180
Gentlemen, please!

577
01:06:03,250 --> 01:06:05,950
You will not bring your countries'
quarrels into these chambers!

578
01:06:06,020 --> 01:06:07,960
The only way to deal with this...

579
01:06:08,030 --> 01:06:10,860
is for each country to
come up with its own solution!

580
01:06:17,270 --> 01:06:19,400
Inspector,
we're ready to move out.

581
01:06:19,470 --> 01:06:22,800
We can leave for Cagliostro
at any time.

582
01:06:23,610 --> 01:06:25,270
We won't be moving out.

583
01:06:25,340 --> 01:06:29,970
As soon as they choose my replacement,
we'll be off the Lupin case.

584
01:06:30,050 --> 01:06:32,710
All of you,
get ready to go home.

585
01:06:42,830 --> 01:06:44,490
<i>It's me.</i>

586
01:06:45,330 --> 01:06:47,560
- Food.
- Thanks.

587
01:06:47,630 --> 01:06:50,760
- How is he?
- His fever seems to have dropped.

588
01:06:50,830 --> 01:06:53,270
Thanks to the treatment
you gave him.

589
01:06:53,340 --> 01:06:55,740
If you want to thank anyone,
thank the dog.

590
01:06:55,810 --> 01:07:00,680
That old dog doesn't like anyone,
but he won't leave that man's side.

591
01:07:00,740 --> 01:07:04,650
If not for that,
I never would have hidden you here.

592
01:07:14,220 --> 01:07:16,120
Hello, Karl.

593
01:07:16,190 --> 01:07:17,750
He's awake.

594
01:07:17,830 --> 01:07:20,320
Lupin, how do you feel?

595
01:07:22,470 --> 01:07:25,530
Jigen. Goemon.
It's been a while.

596
01:07:25,600 --> 01:07:28,070
A while?
What's he talking about?

597
01:07:28,140 --> 01:07:31,010
I think his wounds have
temporarily confused his memory.

598
01:07:31,080 --> 01:07:34,980
Karl, why aren't you
with your owner today?

599
01:07:36,180 --> 01:07:39,710
How do you know
that dog's name?

600
01:07:39,780 --> 01:07:43,950
The only other person besides me
who knows it's Karl is Princess Clarisse.

601
01:07:44,020 --> 01:07:46,120
Clarisse?

602
01:07:46,190 --> 01:07:50,860
So your owner's name is Clarisse.

603
01:07:50,930 --> 01:07:53,020
Clarisse...

604
01:07:56,500 --> 01:07:57,990
Lupin?

605
01:07:58,070 --> 01:08:01,060
Jigen! How many days?
How many days has it been?

606
01:08:01,140 --> 01:08:03,070
Uh, three.

607
01:08:03,140 --> 01:08:05,770
What? That means
the wedding's tomorrow.

608
01:08:05,840 --> 01:08:07,830
I have to—

609
01:08:08,610 --> 01:08:11,510
Don't push yourself.
You'll reopen your wounds.

610
01:08:11,580 --> 01:08:14,980
Food. Bring me food.

611
01:08:15,050 --> 01:08:16,920
Food?
Some porridge, maybe?

612
01:08:16,990 --> 01:08:20,390
I've lost a lot of blood.
Anything'll do. Bring me a feast.

613
01:08:20,460 --> 01:08:22,760
Well, that's easy
for you to say, but—

614
01:08:22,830 --> 01:08:24,590
I'll see what I can do.

615
01:08:30,000 --> 01:08:32,130
You damn fool!
Don't eat so fast.

616
01:08:32,200 --> 01:08:34,670
Your body can't take that much.

617
01:08:34,740 --> 01:08:38,370
Shut up! Gimme 12 hours
and I'll be as fit as a jet plane!

618
01:08:49,850 --> 01:08:52,020
See? I told you so.
Need a wash basin?

619
01:08:54,060 --> 01:08:55,960
What?

620
01:08:57,960 --> 01:08:59,690
He says now he'll sleep.

621
01:09:02,700 --> 01:09:06,290
I see.
He did it for Princess Clarisse.

622
01:09:06,370 --> 01:09:09,240
But now that
Lupin's hurt this badly—

623
01:09:09,310 --> 01:09:12,610
You seem to be connected with
Miss Clarisse from the past, old man.

624
01:09:12,680 --> 01:09:16,080
I tended the palace gardens.

625
01:09:16,150 --> 01:09:19,140
Princess Clarisse
loved plants as a child.

626
01:09:19,220 --> 01:09:23,150
When her family died and
she was sent off to the convent...

627
01:09:23,220 --> 01:09:25,660
she gave me this dog.

628
01:09:25,720 --> 01:09:30,560
He must have smelled the
princess's scent on Lupin's body.

629
01:09:30,630 --> 01:09:34,330
But, then, how could he have
known the dog's name?

630
01:09:34,400 --> 01:09:37,700
I dunno. Lupin can be charmed
by women really easily, but—

631
01:09:37,770 --> 01:09:40,500
- It wasn't like that.
- What, you're awake?

632
01:09:41,910 --> 01:09:44,530
It happened 10 years ago.

633
01:09:45,210 --> 01:09:49,610
I was a young hotshot kid
who was just starting out on his own.

634
01:09:57,720 --> 01:09:59,690
<i>I acted like an idiot.</i>

635
01:09:59,760 --> 01:10:03,520
<i>To top it all off,
I decided to go after the Goat bills.</i>

636
01:10:12,700 --> 01:10:17,610
<i>Somehow, I made it to the shore,
but I could move no further.</i>

637
01:10:22,080 --> 01:10:24,840
Karl? What's wrong, Karl?

638
01:10:33,960 --> 01:10:37,420
<i>I thought my number
had finally come up.</i>

639
01:10:41,970 --> 01:10:43,490
Water.

640
01:10:55,680 --> 01:10:58,410
As her trembling hands
gave me the water...

641
01:10:58,480 --> 01:11:02,720
I noticed a ring on her finger,
sparkling in the light.

642
01:11:02,790 --> 01:11:04,450
I'm ashamed to say this...

643
01:11:04,520 --> 01:11:07,390
but until I saw the ring again,
I'd forgotten completely about it.

644
01:11:15,470 --> 01:11:17,730
That was Fujiko's bike.

645
01:11:17,800 --> 01:11:19,700
It's a clipping from today's paper.

646
01:11:19,770 --> 01:11:22,600
"An archbishop is coming from
the Vatican tomorrow morning...

647
01:11:22,670 --> 01:11:24,660
to perform the wedding."

648
01:11:34,750 --> 01:11:37,410
I'm off the case!

649
01:11:37,490 --> 01:11:38,610
Fujiko?

650
01:11:39,390 --> 01:11:42,090
What? Lupin's gonna hit
the wedding? Really?

651
01:11:42,160 --> 01:11:46,060
If you're after Lupin, your superiors
won't mind your going in there, right?

652
01:11:47,030 --> 01:11:49,560
That's right!
That's how we'll play it.

653
01:12:13,020 --> 01:12:14,960
We're in a hurry. Move!

654
01:12:15,030 --> 01:12:18,150
Forget it.
Everything past here is all jammed up.

655
01:12:18,230 --> 01:12:20,860
There was a landslide
seven kilometers up the road.

656
01:12:20,930 --> 01:12:25,160
Isn't there some other road?
We're going to be late.

657
01:12:25,840 --> 01:12:28,900
Would you by any chance
be the archbishop?

658
01:12:28,970 --> 01:12:34,840
Ah, yes, you are.
Would you please bless this lamb?

659
01:12:36,650 --> 01:12:41,050
Say, you're a local, right?
There any other roads to Cagliostro?

660
01:12:41,120 --> 01:12:43,590
If you don't mind a country road,
there's one that way.

661
01:12:43,650 --> 01:12:44,750
We're saved!

662
01:12:44,820 --> 01:12:47,190
Can you show us the way?
C'mon, hop in.

663
01:12:47,260 --> 01:12:51,350
Yes.
Anything for the archbishop.

664
01:12:57,230 --> 01:13:00,000
C'mon, push! One more hill
and we're in Cagliostro.

665
01:13:00,070 --> 01:13:02,560
We've gotta get there
by nightfall.

666
01:13:15,290 --> 01:13:19,220
Is it really such a good idea
to have TV cameras in here?

667
01:13:19,290 --> 01:13:21,380
His Excellency wishes
to show the world...

668
01:13:21,460 --> 01:13:24,860
that this is a proper
and legal marriage.

669
01:13:25,760 --> 01:13:28,230
The archbishop has arrived.

670
01:13:35,140 --> 01:13:37,110
Do you suppose
Lupin will come?

671
01:13:37,170 --> 01:13:40,110
My Shadows are guarding the bride.

672
01:13:40,180 --> 01:13:43,340
All you need worry about
is guarding the front gate.

673
01:14:44,340 --> 01:14:48,240
The time has come
for light and shadow to be united.

674
01:14:48,310 --> 01:14:50,300
Come, Clarisse.

675
01:16:17,470 --> 01:16:19,870
Bring forward the proof...

676
01:16:19,940 --> 01:16:25,500
that these are truly noble members
of the ancient bloodline of Cagliostro.

677
01:16:30,910 --> 01:16:33,880
In accordance to the old custom...

678
01:16:33,950 --> 01:16:37,350
you shall exchange rings
and recite your vows.

679
01:16:38,020 --> 01:16:43,980
Clarisse d' Cagliostro, daughter
of the Grand Duke of Cagliostro...

680
01:16:44,060 --> 01:16:46,830
do you have no objection
to this marriage?

681
01:16:46,900 --> 01:16:50,390
Silence will be taken as agreement.

682
01:17:08,990 --> 01:17:11,920
God's blessing upon you.

683
01:17:11,990 --> 01:17:13,890
I object!

684
01:17:15,290 --> 01:17:19,390
This wedding is soiled
by the count's desires.

685
01:17:33,040 --> 01:17:35,100
- A curse!
- Don't panic.

686
01:17:35,180 --> 01:17:37,770
The meddlers have simply
made their appearance.

687
01:17:55,330 --> 01:17:59,360
In the name of the dead
who lie beneath this castle...

688
01:17:59,440 --> 01:18:02,240
<i>I have come to take your bride.</i>

689
01:18:02,310 --> 01:18:04,570
- We can't have the wedding now.
- Step back.

690
01:18:04,640 --> 01:18:06,300
This will make fine entertainment.

691
01:18:07,910 --> 01:18:11,210
<i>Clarisse, I've come for you.</i>

692
01:18:16,620 --> 01:18:18,280
Ghosts!

693
01:18:18,360 --> 01:18:21,690
This is terrible, ladies and gentlemen.
It's Lupin! Lupin has appeared.

694
01:18:21,760 --> 01:18:23,250
Stop the broadcast.

695
01:18:23,330 --> 01:18:26,190
<i>- What are you doing?</i>
- Move out!

696
01:18:29,330 --> 01:18:32,200
<i>Clarisse! Clarisse!</i>

697
01:18:32,270 --> 01:18:34,860
<i>Poor girl.
They've drugged you, haven't they?</i>

698
01:18:34,940 --> 01:18:38,430
<i>The damned count.
He didn't want you able to speak.</i>

699
01:18:47,250 --> 01:18:50,950
- Mr. Thief!
- No, dear. Stay back.

700
01:18:51,890 --> 01:18:55,150
You were a fool, Lupin.
Finish the others!

701
01:18:57,190 --> 01:19:00,530
Clarisse.
Don't cry, Clarisse.

702
01:19:02,130 --> 01:19:04,930
<i>I'm coming for you now.</i>

703
01:19:11,540 --> 01:19:13,510
Money?

704
01:19:13,580 --> 01:19:16,440
<i>Do you like my present, Count?</i>

705
01:19:16,510 --> 01:19:18,000
Excellency!

706
01:19:18,080 --> 01:19:22,520
<i>They're the counterfeit bills you made.
Take it as payment for the rings.</i>

707
01:19:23,550 --> 01:19:27,320
Damn him! Find him!
He's somewhere in here.

708
01:19:29,090 --> 01:19:30,530
Told you I'd get 'em.

709
01:19:30,590 --> 01:19:33,090
You— Lupin?

710
01:19:33,760 --> 01:19:35,360
Mr. Thief!

711
01:19:35,430 --> 01:19:37,330
How dare you make a fool of me!

712
01:19:37,400 --> 01:19:41,390
Cool off, O pedophiliac count!
Watch out before you get burned.

713
01:20:08,100 --> 01:20:09,460
Lupin!

714
01:20:09,530 --> 01:20:11,860
Sorry for the delay,
ladies and gentlemen.

715
01:20:11,940 --> 01:20:15,630
We'll resume our broadcast now.
The wedding ceremony is in an uproar!

716
01:20:16,570 --> 01:20:18,440
- Well, if you'll excuse me.
- Die!

717
01:20:26,120 --> 01:20:28,240
After them!
Don't let them escape!

718
01:20:28,320 --> 01:20:31,750
Lupin's escaped.
The count is following him in a rage.

719
01:20:32,560 --> 01:20:34,220
And here come the police!

720
01:20:35,630 --> 01:20:37,790
Lupin's under the altar.

721
01:20:37,860 --> 01:20:40,490
All together! Charge!

722
01:20:42,170 --> 01:20:45,260
Zenigata's men are opening
a path to the altar.

723
01:20:45,340 --> 01:20:48,900
And here come the royal guards
with Captain Gustav in the lead.

724
01:20:48,970 --> 01:20:50,630
Rear guard, deploy!

725
01:20:55,310 --> 01:20:58,250
Stand your ground!
Justice is on our side.

726
01:20:58,310 --> 01:21:00,480
This is a really fierce fight, folks!

727
01:21:00,550 --> 01:21:03,080
What could be under the altar?

728
01:21:04,020 --> 01:21:06,510
It's a stairway!
There's a hole leading underground.

729
01:21:06,590 --> 01:21:10,920
Could Lupin be in that hole?
Let's take a camera in and find out.

730
01:21:11,830 --> 01:21:13,490
Curse you, Lupin!

731
01:21:14,830 --> 01:21:17,820
<i>-Lupin!</i>
- What's that idiot doing?

732
01:21:17,900 --> 01:21:19,930
He's disobeying orders.
Recall him!

733
01:21:20,000 --> 01:21:22,530
This is a satellite broadcast.
It's too late.

734
01:21:23,370 --> 01:21:25,270
What can this be?

735
01:21:25,340 --> 01:21:28,500
Why, it looks just
like the National Mint!

736
01:21:28,580 --> 01:21:30,600
And what do I see over there?

737
01:21:32,380 --> 01:21:35,820
<i>Good grief! Japanese money!
It must be counterfeit.</i>

738
01:21:35,890 --> 01:21:39,290
- Lord, what a bad actor.
<i>- What a terrible discovery!</i>

739
01:21:39,360 --> 01:21:42,520
<i>Look. Counterfeit money
from all over the world.</i>

740
01:21:42,590 --> 01:21:45,530
<i>I came in after Lupin and
found this terrible crime.</i>

741
01:21:45,600 --> 01:21:46,720
<i>What should I do?</i>

742
01:21:59,140 --> 01:22:01,080
First of all,
let's get you out of the castle.

743
01:22:01,140 --> 01:22:02,630
Go to it, Jigen. Goemon.

744
01:22:02,710 --> 01:22:05,110
Leave this to us.
we'll hold 'em off here.

745
01:22:10,290 --> 01:22:14,150
Please be careful.
And you, Sir Jigen.

746
01:22:14,920 --> 01:22:16,860
Please be sure
to come back from this alive.

747
01:22:16,930 --> 01:22:18,830
I'll never forget your kindness.

748
01:22:18,900 --> 01:22:20,760
You'd better go.

749
01:22:23,030 --> 01:22:24,900
Clarisse, hurry.

750
01:22:24,970 --> 01:22:26,900
Coming!

751
01:22:32,080 --> 01:22:34,070
SirJigen, huh?

752
01:22:34,140 --> 01:22:35,940
She's lovely.

753
01:22:40,420 --> 01:22:42,610
Let's do some damage.

754
01:22:50,030 --> 01:22:52,720
This sword you face tonight
is like no other.

755
01:22:52,800 --> 01:22:55,460
Curse you, Lupin.
You haven't won yet.

756
01:22:58,200 --> 01:23:00,640
We'll take care of the castle,
My Lord.

757
01:23:18,660 --> 01:23:21,450
- Do your wounds hurt?
- Nah, they were just scratches.

758
01:23:21,520 --> 01:23:23,490
Now, let's get across this.

759
01:23:29,130 --> 01:23:32,260
Two goats facing each other.

760
01:23:37,040 --> 01:23:39,940
When you put them together,
there's an inscription in Capran.

761
01:23:40,010 --> 01:23:42,910
Light and shadow—

762
01:23:42,980 --> 01:23:45,310
It's too worn. I can't read it.

763
01:23:45,380 --> 01:23:47,850
"When light and
shadow are joined...

764
01:23:47,920 --> 01:23:50,680
face the Goat on high
who faces the sun...

765
01:23:50,750 --> 01:23:53,090
and tells time
and place me in its eyes."

766
01:23:53,160 --> 01:23:55,890
They're old words that have been
passed down through my family.

767
01:23:55,960 --> 01:23:57,620
Are they any help?

768
01:23:57,690 --> 01:24:00,460
Indeed, they are.
The mystery is solved.

769
01:24:02,730 --> 01:24:04,630
The count!
C'mon, this way.

770
01:24:10,240 --> 01:24:13,140
They slipped into the clock tower
machinery room. Moor the boat.

771
01:24:27,660 --> 01:24:29,420
There they are.

772
01:24:29,490 --> 01:24:31,480
He's here.

773
01:24:37,830 --> 01:24:39,500
Forget this.

774
01:24:40,400 --> 01:24:44,310
Turn off the lasers. Fools!
Do they think they can leave here?

775
01:25:02,860 --> 01:25:04,380
- Scared?

776
01:25:04,460 --> 01:25:07,020
Good girl. Let's go!

777
01:25:10,700 --> 01:25:11,860
Don't let 'em go!

778
01:25:29,420 --> 01:25:31,010
Don't look!

779
01:25:32,590 --> 01:25:34,180
We can't go this way.

780
01:25:34,260 --> 01:25:36,890
You men use the stairs.

781
01:25:43,630 --> 01:25:45,620
Stay here.
I'm going to block the entrance.

782
01:25:45,700 --> 01:25:48,330
- Be careful!
- I'll be right back.

783
01:25:59,620 --> 01:26:01,110
There he is!

784
01:26:22,100 --> 01:26:24,470
Mr. Thief! Behind you!

785
01:26:29,410 --> 01:26:30,900
Hiya, Count!

786
01:26:31,880 --> 01:26:34,610
You little rat. I'll skewer you.

787
01:26:34,680 --> 01:26:37,090
Time for the finale, Count.

788
01:27:03,450 --> 01:27:04,940
One more time!

789
01:27:13,090 --> 01:27:16,420
Hey, Caggy!
Come and get me.

790
01:27:25,130 --> 01:27:26,970
Mr. Thief!

791
01:27:34,510 --> 01:27:37,280
I'll finish you off first.

792
01:27:37,350 --> 01:27:38,970
Clarisse, run!

793
01:27:39,050 --> 01:27:41,450
I'll be right there!

794
01:28:07,510 --> 01:28:11,380
And just how far
can you run, Clarisse?

795
01:28:17,490 --> 01:28:20,510
Well, now what?

796
01:28:21,590 --> 01:28:23,320
Can't you run any further?

797
01:28:24,160 --> 01:28:27,820
The Cagliostro bloodline ends here.
Die, Clarisse.

798
01:28:27,900 --> 01:28:30,590
Wait, Count!
I'll make a deal.

799
01:28:30,670 --> 01:28:34,000
Too late.
Watch as I kill the girl.

800
01:28:34,070 --> 01:28:35,560
Listen to me!

801
01:28:36,370 --> 01:28:38,670
I'll tell you
the secret of the rings.

802
01:28:38,740 --> 01:28:41,370
The treasure will be yours
to do with as you please.

803
01:28:41,440 --> 01:28:44,850
But let the girl go.
Set her free.

804
01:28:44,910 --> 01:28:47,780
Look. You see the goat crest
on the clock face?

805
01:28:47,850 --> 01:28:50,750
That's the goat which
faces the sun and tells time.

806
01:28:50,820 --> 01:28:53,720
There's a hole
in each eye for the rings.

807
01:28:53,790 --> 01:28:56,190
I'll give you the rings.

808
01:28:56,260 --> 01:28:59,060
However, if you kill the girl,
I'll throw them in the lake...

809
01:28:59,130 --> 01:29:01,100
and then I'll kill you.

810
01:29:29,660 --> 01:29:33,220
That's far enough, thank you.
Send Clarisse inside.

811
01:29:33,300 --> 01:29:35,790
All right. I see.

812
01:29:42,810 --> 01:29:47,000
Lupin. I still had one ace
up my sleeve to play.

813
01:29:48,210 --> 01:29:49,970
Come on.

814
01:29:53,820 --> 01:29:56,680
They're real, all right.
I have the rings.

815
01:29:56,750 --> 01:29:59,740
And now I'll pay you
for solving the mystery.

816
01:30:03,160 --> 01:30:05,420
Let me go!

817
01:30:05,490 --> 01:30:07,430
Clarisse!

818
01:30:10,300 --> 01:30:11,290
Let me go!

819
01:31:41,690 --> 01:31:43,020
The clock tower!

820
01:31:53,540 --> 01:31:55,440
Excellency...

821
01:32:31,840 --> 01:32:33,240
What's happening?

822
01:33:00,200 --> 01:33:03,140
Cagliostro is finished.

823
01:33:03,810 --> 01:33:05,240
Kill me.

824
01:33:05,310 --> 01:33:07,740
I don't take lives without reason.

825
01:33:56,890 --> 01:34:00,290
- Mr. Thief?
- Can you stand? Look.

826
01:34:23,720 --> 01:34:25,810
The hidden treasure.

827
01:34:26,520 --> 01:34:30,720
A Roman city,
hidden at the bottom of the lake.

828
01:34:30,790 --> 01:34:33,230
When the Romans were
driven from here...

829
01:34:33,300 --> 01:34:35,390
they flooded the city
with the floodgate.

830
01:34:35,460 --> 01:34:38,460
Your ancestors secretly inherited it.

831
01:34:47,710 --> 01:34:50,980
This is a treasure for all mankind.

832
01:34:51,050 --> 01:34:53,610
Too big for my pocket anyway.

833
01:35:11,470 --> 01:35:14,330
Interpol finally got off its fat butt.

834
01:35:29,550 --> 01:35:31,420
Are you going to leave now?

835
01:35:32,190 --> 01:35:36,750
Well, there are some very
scary men coming, you see.

836
01:35:38,760 --> 01:35:40,420
Take me with you.

837
01:35:40,500 --> 01:35:42,930
I know I can't be a thief now,
but I can learn!

838
01:35:43,000 --> 01:35:45,160
I—

839
01:35:45,900 --> 01:35:48,800
Please, I want to go with you.

840
01:35:51,770 --> 01:35:53,500
Clarisse.

841
01:36:02,320 --> 01:36:04,410
Don't be ridiculous.

842
01:36:04,490 --> 01:36:06,680
You want to go back
into the darkness again?

843
01:36:06,760 --> 01:36:09,350
You've finally made it out
into the sunlight, haven't you?

844
01:36:09,430 --> 01:36:12,830
Listen, your whole life
is starting now.

845
01:36:12,900 --> 01:36:15,800
You shouldn't want to turn into
a terrible person like me.

846
01:36:15,860 --> 01:36:18,770
Oh, yeah! if you ever need help,
just let me know.

847
01:36:18,830 --> 01:36:22,600
I'll come running from
anywhere on Earth to save you.

848
01:36:32,250 --> 01:36:33,910
Karl!

849
01:36:33,980 --> 01:36:36,820
Oh, Karl!

850
01:36:36,890 --> 01:36:39,380
- Princess Clarisse!
- It's you!

851
01:36:49,500 --> 01:36:51,490
- Mr. Thief!
- Until next time.

852
01:36:52,330 --> 01:36:54,270
Hiya, Princess!

853
01:36:56,170 --> 01:36:58,070
Mr. Thief!

854
01:36:58,140 --> 01:37:02,040
Stay well, Clarisse. Adieu!

855
01:37:04,480 --> 01:37:08,110
Thank you!
Good bye, all of you!

856
01:37:08,180 --> 01:37:11,410
Adieu! Adieu!

857
01:37:24,100 --> 01:37:26,260
Blast it!
I was one step behind him.

858
01:37:26,340 --> 01:37:28,300
Lupin managed to steal
something again.

859
01:37:28,370 --> 01:37:33,640
No, he didn't steal anything.
All he did was fight for me.

860
01:37:33,710 --> 01:37:37,110
No, he stole
something quite precious.

861
01:37:38,380 --> 01:37:40,040
Your heart.

862
01:37:42,250 --> 01:37:43,240
Yes.

863
01:37:44,090 --> 01:37:46,080
Well, if you'll excuse me.

864
01:37:50,830 --> 01:37:54,160
Follow Lupin! Follow him
to the ends of the Earth!

865
01:38:13,020 --> 01:38:16,450
They all seem like such nice people.

866
01:38:16,520 --> 01:38:20,920
I feel as though
I know that man from long ago.

867
01:38:21,790 --> 01:38:25,320
Lupin, someday—
I know we'll meet again someday.

868
01:38:30,170 --> 01:38:32,690
She's a nice kid.

869
01:38:34,740 --> 01:38:37,710
You could stay if you want.

870
01:38:40,910 --> 01:38:42,340
Oh? Fujiko!

871
01:38:42,410 --> 01:38:45,240
Lupin!
Take a look at what I scored.

872
01:38:45,310 --> 01:38:48,010
Hey!
The counterfeit printing plates!

873
01:38:48,080 --> 01:38:50,880
- Can we be friends?
- See you!

874
01:38:50,950 --> 01:38:54,860
Hey, wait! Wait for me!

875
01:38:58,030 --> 01:39:00,890
It's the Old Man again.

876
01:39:00,960 --> 01:39:03,400
Lupin!
You won't escape this time.

